Third-party components
======================

VoiceRSS API client (lib/VoiceRss.php)
  Uses the VoiceRSS text-to-speech HTTP API.
  Service terms: https://www.voicerss.org/
  You must supply your own API key to use that service.

External data sources
  - api.weather.gov (NWS alerts)
  - www.nhc.noaa.gov (optional cyclone advisories)
  - earthquake.usgs.gov (optional USGS earthquake feed)
  - services3.arcgis.com (optional NIFC WFIGS wildfire perimeters)

External runtime dependencies (not bundled)
  - PHP, sox, Asterisk/AllStar, libespeak-ng1
  - Optional: gpsd, asl3-tts, Pushover (CPU alarms via Linux thermal/hwmon on Pi, ARM64, x86_64)

Sound files are shipped as `.ulaw` in `sounds/` and installed to `/usr/share/cap-alert/sounds/`.
Optional fallbacks: Asterisk wx/digits/silence/rpt directories (ulaw only).
